7.    Our gender pay audit data 
 
7.1 The mean and median gender pay gap 
 
The mean gender pay gap adds together the hourly pay rates of all male  and female pay and 
divides this by the respective number of male or female employees.  The gap is calculated by 
taking the difference between the male and female averages and dividing that by the mean hourly 
rate for males. 
 
The median arranges the hourly rates from highest to lowest and finds the point in the middle of 
that range. 
 
 
 

 

 

