7.2 The mean and median bonus gender pay gap 
 
The mean bonus gender pay gap adds together bonus payments for all male and female pay 
and divides this by the respective number of male or female employees.  The gap is calculated 
by taking the difference between the male and female averages and dividing that by the mean 
bonus payment for males. 
 
The median arranges the bonus payments from highest to lowest and finds the point in the middle 
of that range. 
 
 
 

 

 

